nnenhof beliebte Fotosujets. Rund um das Gebäude finden sich zudem hübsche begrünte Nischen sowie südlich die Polyterrasse, die einen herrlichen Blick über die Dächer der Altstadt eröffnet.</p>','<p>If you walk from Zurich Main Station towards Central and the River Limmat, you may just be able to make out the main building of the ETH Zurich on the hillside. To the left of the green dome of Zurich University, sharp eyes will be able to spot a large, darker dome, which today is the distinguishing feature of the ETH Swiss Federal Institute of Technology.</p><p>The original building was constructed in 1864 by Gottfried Semper, who was also responsible for the Semperoper in Dresden, which bears his name. In those days, the ETH was referred to as the &ldquo;Polytechnikum&rdquo; (Polytechnic School) and at the time it was a truly monumental building for both Zurich and Switzerland. After it was extended by Gustav Gull between 1914 and 1925, the only part of the original Semper building still remaining was the façade overlooking the city. Gustav Gull &ndash; who had already built the National Museum next to Zurich Main Station &ndash; made extensive changes, both inside and out. The above-mentioned dome, for example, was added by him.</p><p>It is well worth visiting the ETH, the interior of which is particularly beautiful. Popular photo motives include the focusTerra tower and the inner courtyard. All around the building, there are also pretty niches abounding in greenery, while to the south, the Polyterrasse offers a magnificent view over the rooftops of the Old Town.</p>','<p>Lorsque vous quittez la gare centrale de Zurich en direction de la Limmat et de la place &laquo;&nbsp;Central&nbsp;&raquo;, vous apercevez le bâtiment principal de l&rsquo;École polytechnique fédérale de Zurich&nbsp;: avec un peu d&rsquo;habileté, vous découvrirez sa grande coupole foncée, aujourd&rsquo;hui emblème de l&rsquo;EPF, à gauche de la coupole verte de l&rsquo;Université de Zurich.</p><p>L&rsquo;édifice d&rsquo;origine datant de 1864 a été conçu par Gottfried Semper, architecte de l&rsquo;opéra Semperoper de Dresde. A l&rsquo;époque, l&rsquo;EPF (appelée alors &laquo;&nbsp;Polytechnikum&nbsp;&raquo;) fut un véritable bâtiment monumental pour Zurich et la Suisse. Après l&rsquo;agrandissement de l&rsquo;édifice par l&rsquo;architecte Gustav Gull en 1925, seule la façade donnant sur le centre-ville témoigne de ses origines. Gustav Gull, qui a également construit le Musée national près de la gare centrale de Zurich, a opéré des modifications majeures, à l&rsquo;intérieur comme à l&rsquo;extérieur de la construction &ndash; par exemple la coupole mentionnée ci-dessus.</p><p>Une visite de l&rsquo;EPF vaut la peine, surtout l&rsquo;intérieur est magnifique. La tour Focus Terra et la cour intérieure sont des sujets photo très appréciés. Autour de l&rsquo;édifice se trouvent de belles niches végétalisées ainsi que la Polyterrasse orientée sud qui offre une vue magnifique sur les toits de la vieille ville.</p>','<p>Andando dalla Stazione Centrale verso Central e la Limmat, con uno sguardo attento si può scorgere l&rsquo;edificio principale dell&rsquo;ETH di Zurigo sulla collina. A sinistra, accanto alla cupola verde dell&rsquo;Università di Zurigo, gli occhi più allenati trovano la grande cupola scura dell&rsquo;ETH, oggi simbolo del politecnico.</p><p>La costruzione originale fu realizzata nel 1864 da Gottfried Semper, autore anche della Semperoper di Dresda. All&rsquo;epoca, l&rsquo;ETH era una vera e propria struttura monumentale per Zurigo e per la Svizzera. In seguito a un ampliamento da parte di Gustav Gull, dell&rsquo;edificio iniziale è rimasta solo la facciata che dà sulla città. Nel 1925, l&rsquo;architetto Gustav Gull, autore anche del Museo Nazionale Zurigo, accanto alla Stazione Centrale, ha cambiato molte cose dentro e fuori. La cupola di cui sopra, per esempio, è stata una sua idea.</p><p>Vale la pena visitare l&rsquo;ETH, splendido soprattutto al suo interno: la torre FocusTerra e il cortile interno sono soggetti fotografici molto amati. Attorno all&rsquo;edificio si trovano, inoltre, graziosi angoli verdi, mentre a sud c&rsquo;è la Polyterrasse, che regala una vista incantevole sui tetti del centro storico.</p>','Hauptgebäude ETH Zürich','Main Building of the ETH Zurich','Bâtiment principal EPFZ','Edificio principale dell’ETH di Zurigo','Eines der Wahrzeichen von Zürich ist die auf einer Terrasse thronende Eidgenössische Technische Hochschule.','One of Zurich’s landmarks is the Federal Institute of Technology on the hill overlooking the city. ','L’École polytechnique fédérale surmontant avec majesté une terrasse est l’un des emblèmes de Zurich.','Uno dei simboli di Zurigo è il Politecnico Federale di Zurigo, che troneggia su una terrazza.','https://cdn.zuerich.com/sites/default/files/web_zuerich_eth_hauptgebaeude_1280x960_24299.jpg','2019-01-03 16:57:01 +0100','Fertiggestellt: 1864','Year completed: 1864','Achevé en : 1864','Fine dei lavori: 1864','CH','Zürich',8092,'Rämistrasse 101','https://www.zuerich.com/node/313748',47.376537400000,8.548086100000,'POINT (47.3765374 8.548086100000001)',1,'+41 44 632 11 11','<p>Montag bis Freitag, 06.00 &ndash; 22.00 Uhr<br />Samstag und Sonntag, 08.00 &ndash; 17.00 Uhr</p>','<p>Monday &ndash; Friday, 6am &ndash; 10pm<br />Saturday &amp; Sunday, 8am &ndash; 5pm</p>','<p>Du lundi au vendredi, 6h &ndash; 22h<br />Samedi et dimanche, 8h &ndash; 17h&nbsp;</p>','<p>Da lunedì a venerdì 06.00 &ndash; 22.00<br />Sabato e domenica 08.00 &ndash; 17.00</p>','Monday,Tuesday,Wednesday,Thursday,Friday,Saturday,Sunday','https://cdn.zuerich.com/sites/default/files/web_zuerich_eth_hauptgebaeude_1280x960_24298.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
